<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Long_hair&action=edit&section=1.php.html" title="Edit section: Transferred meaning">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Transferred_meaning">Transferred meaning</span></h2>
<p>The traditional connotation of "long hair" in <a href="English_language" title="English language">English</a> meant, roughly, someone artistically knowledgeable or wise, an <a href="Aesthete" title="Aesthete" class="mw-redirect">aesthete</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-OED_13-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-OED-13"><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup> As a descriptive term, it has been applied to <a href="Merovingians" title="Merovingians" class="mw-redirect">Merovingians</a> and <a href="Classical_music" title="Classical music">classical music</a> enthusiasts, as well as hippies and aesthetes.<sup id="cite_ref-OED_13-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-OED-13"><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Long_hair&action=edit&section=2.php.html" title="Edit section: Hair lengths">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Hair_lengths">Hair lengths</span></h2>
